orangelight.title: Location label changes on availability load

comments.body:
The location is right, the label differs. The first one comes from the bibdata holding_locations lookup which is part of the https://github.com/pulibrary/orangelight/blob/ace3e1ba6188b85a091eac310adb82b18ac1cfe2/app/services/physical_holdings_markup_builder.rb 
and the HoldingRequestAdapter 

https://github.com/pulibrary/orangelight/blob/ace3e1ba6188b85a091eac310adb82b18ac1cfe2/app/services/holding_requests_adapter.rb#L112. 

The second one comes from the api call getting only $c. 
`AVA    
0| 9918888023506421 8| 22260730640006421 a| 01PRI_INST b| recap c| Remote Storage: Mendel Music Library use only d| LS- 9073 e| available f| 1 g| 0 j| qk k| 8 p| 1 q| ReCAP`

If we want to follow the same pattern with production and display the same location label we would need to:

1.Remove location['library']['label'] from https://github.com/pulibrary/orangelight/blob/ace3e1ba6188b85a091eac310adb82b18ac1cfe2/app/services/holding_requests_adapter.rb#L114

2.Update https://github.com/pulibrary/bibdata/blob/1fbf110c3fc595d301b1ed0a592bbd8aff1f407c/app/services/location_data_service.rb#L35 to equal only to the external name and not append the library_record.label. 

I will work on a branch for this solution and index a couple of records.

orangelight.title: Availability not populating for all the search results

comments.body:
The records that dont display availability they all have etas location in the api call. https://bibdata-alma-staging.princeton.edu/bibliographic/9929723813506421/availability.json `{"9929723813506421":{"other":{"on_reserve":"N","location":"etas","label":"ETAS","status_label":"Available","cdl":false,"holding_type":"other","id":"other"}}}`
https://catalog-alma-qa.princeton.edu/catalog/9929723813506421

I also think that when we ran the index @tpendragon had removed elfs and etas from the bibdata db so they don't get indexed in the holdings1_display. For example this record includes in the holdings1_display only firestone$stacks. `"holdings_1display": "{\"22159277990006421\":{\"location_code\":\"firestone$stacks\",\"location\":\"Firestone Library - Firestone Library Stacks\",\"library\":\"Firestone Library\",\"call_number\":\"PN1995.9.M86 M874 2000\",\"call_number_browse\":\"PN1995.9.M86 M874 2000\",\"items\":[{\"holding_id\":\"22159277990006421\",\"id\":\"23159277970006421\",\"status_at_load\":\"1\",\"barcode\":\"32101039113301\",\"copy_number\":\"1\"}]}}",` 

and not etas which is the temporary location based on the api call `<in_temp_location>true</in_temp_location>
            <temp_library desc="Electronic Access">online</temp_library>
            <temp_location desc="ETAS Non Circulating">etas</temp_location>`

Did we remove displaying availability for temporary locations based on the api call?

Reviewing this issue with @mzelesky 
If an item is in a temp location and it is the only item on a holding then the only AVA returned is for the temp location and it doesn't include a holding_id ($8).
`tag=\"AVA\"><subfield code=\"0\">9929723813506421</subfield><subfield code=\"a\">01PRI_INST</subfield><subfield code=\"b\">online</subfield><subfield code=\"c\">ETAS</subfield><subfield code=\"d\">PN1995.9.M86 M874 2000</subfield><subfield code=\"e\">available</subfield><subfield code=\"f\">1</subfield><subfield code=\"g\">0</subfield><subfield code=\"j\">etas</subfield><subfield code=\"k\">0</subfield><subfield code=\"p\">1</subfield><subfield code=\"q\">Electronic Access</subfield></datafield>`

If there are some items on a holding in a temp location and others in the permanent location then there are 2 AVAs returned
`tag=\"AVA\"><subfield code=\"0\">9930823573506421</subfield><subfield code=\"a\">01PRI_INST</subfield><subfield code=\"b\">online</subfield><subfield code=\"c\">ETAS Non Circ ReCAP</subfield><subfield code=\"d\">DS793 .C48 vol.452</subfield><subfield code=\"e\">available</subfield><subfield code=\"f\">5</subfield><subfield code=\"g\">0</subfield><subfield code=\"j\">etasrcp</subfield><subfield code=\"k\">0</subfield><subfield code=\"p\">1</subfield><subfield code=\"q\">Electronic Access</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=\" \" ind2=\" \" tag=\"AVA\"><subfield code=\"0\">9930823573506421</subfield><subfield code=\"8\">22100002150006421</subfield><subfield code=\"a\">01PRI_INST</subfield><subfield code=\"b\">recap</subfield><subfield code=\"c\">Remote Storage</subfield><subfield code=\"d\">DS793 .C48 vol.452</subfield><subfield code=\"e\">available</subfield><subfield code=\"f\">1</subfield><subfield code=\"g\">0</subfield><subfield code=\"j\">pa</subfield><subfield code=\"k\">0</subfield><subfield code=\"p\">2</subfield><subfield code=\"q\">ReCAP</subfield><subfield code=\"t\">Pt.1-pt.6</subfield></datafield>`

The current approach we have to show availability in the show and search results is to show the calculated availability at the holding level based on the AVA fields. If items are in a temporary location there is not holding id in the AVA. So we cannot have a 'Request' button next to the holding.  

To make this work in Alma we would use a work order like we do for 'CDL' instead of a temporary location.
